<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,752,1243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1023,1049]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was originally described from three localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1067,1128,1024,1050]" name="Laos" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Laos</collectingCountry>
. It is here newly reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[219,326,1062,1088]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, from 
<collectingRegion box="[408,519,1062,1088]" country="Vietnam" name="Nghe An" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Nghe An</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[582,682,1062,1088]" country="Vietnam" name="Ha Tinh" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Ha Tinh</collectingRegion>
provinces both bordering 
<collectingCountry box="[1013,1076,1062,1088]" name="Laos" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Laos</collectingCountry>
. The records of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Polhemus &amp; Andersen" baseAuthorityYear="1984" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexualis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Amemboides sexualis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[319,412,1101,1127]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[425,495,1101,1127]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">China</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng" box="[541,772,1101,1127]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Cheng" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" pagination="203 - 214" refId="ref4631" refString="Cheng, L., Yang, C. M., Li, D. &amp; Liu, H. (2006) Aquatic Heteroptera (Insecta: Gerromorpha and Nepomorpha) from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54 (2), 203 - 214." type="journal article" year="2006">
Cheng 
<emphasis box="[626,686,1101,1126]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zettel, Yang &amp; Tran, 2007)" baseAuthorityName="Zettel, Yang &amp; Tran" baseAuthorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanus">
<emphasis box="[900,1172,1101,1126]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Amemboides yunnanus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zettel, Yang &amp; Tran" firstAuthor="Zettel" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" pagination="223 - 229" refId="ref4851" refString="Zettel, H., Yang, C. M. &amp; Tran, A. D. (2007) Two new species of Amemboa subgenus Amemboides (Heteroptera: Gerridae) from China and Laos. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 55 (2), 223 - 229." type="journal article" year="2007">Zettel, Yang &amp; Tran, 2007</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Zettel" box="[286,622,1140,1166]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Zettel" page="228 - 229" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" pagination="223 - 229" refId="ref4851" refString="Zettel, H., Yang, C. M. &amp; Tran, A. D. (2007) Two new species of Amemboa subgenus Amemboides (Heteroptera: Gerridae) from China and Laos. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 55 (2), 223 - 229." type="journal article" year="2007">
Zettel 
<emphasis box="[365,426,1140,1165]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
2007: 228–229
</bibRefCitation>
). The late instar male nymphs have developed the extended genital segments with the posterolateral projections, but not the setiferation of adult males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
